an understanding of the ongoing tensions in the construction of self with others that
the women experience. We argue that the affirmation of new bonds, control in sharing
the process of 'moving on', and supporting discursive negotiations of privacy are
important considerations for design focused on interpersonal social processes around
the use of digital technology.},
booktitle = {Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems},
