abstract = {Current solutions for enabling touch interaction on existing non-touch LCD screens
require adding additional sensors to the interaction surface. We present uTouch, a
system that detects and classifies touches and hovers without any modification to
the display, and without adding any sensors to the user. Our approach utilizes existing
signals in an LCD that are amplified when a user brings their hand near or touches
the LCD's front panel. These signals are coupled onto the power lines, where they
appear as electromagnetic interference (EMI) which can be sensed using a single device
connected elsewhere on the power line infrastructure. We validate our approach with
