abstract = {We study the design of split keyboards for fast text entry with two thumbs on mobile
touchscreen devices. The layout of KALQ was determined through first studying how
users should grip a device with two hands. We then assigned letters to keys computationally,
using a model of two-thumb tapping. KALQ minimizes thumb travel distance and maximizes
alternation between thumbs. An error correction algorithm was added to help address
linguistic and motor errors. Users reached a rate of 37 words per minute (with a 5%
error rate) after a training program.},
