different perspectives we articulate three cognitive models of behavior change and
consider the potential of these models to support a deeper understanding of behavior
change in serious games. Two of these models -- Information Deficit and Procedural
Rhetoric -- have already been employed in the design of serious games, while the third
-- Emergent Dialogue -- is introduced from the field of Environmental Studies. We
situate this discussion within a context of designing games for public engagement
with issues of environmental sustainability.},
